One extra note about Noah&#39;s suggestion: it assumes you&#39;re starting from 
the (recommended) &#39;deciding-default&#39; example scope, rather than using 
the (deprecated, legacy) &#39;BroadScope&#39; class.

(I think your previous max-links-hops and max-trans-hops settings 
*should* have worked, but since Noah&#39;s approach is the better base for 
the future, getting to the bottom of what might have gone wrong with the 
BroadScope approach isn&#39;t as useful as moving the &#39;deciding&#39; scope.)

- Gordon @ IA

On 1/4/11 11:14 AM, Noah Levitt wrote:
&gt; Here&#39;s one way to crawl seeds only, and not even embedded images or anything, which seems to be what you want. Starting with the default order.xml...
&gt;
&gt; 1. remove the scope rule acceptIfSurtPrefixed
&gt; 2. remove the scope rule acceptIfTranscluded
&gt; 3. add this scope rule right after rejectByDefault
&gt;      &lt;newObject name=&quot;acceptIfSeed&quot; class=&quot;org.archive.crawler.deciderules.SeedAcceptDecideRule&quot;&gt;
&gt;      &lt;/newObject&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Hope this works for you.
&gt;
&gt; Noah
&gt;
&gt;
